            <title>[CAMEL-13541] Race condition in camel-hystrix when xecutionTimeoutInMilliseconds() and onFallback() are used </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-13541</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If e{{xecutionTimeoutInMilliseconds()}} and &lt;tt&gt;onFallback()&lt;/tt&gt; are used together in a camel hystrix definition. When an Hystrix timeout occurs there might be race conditions in modifying the running exchange between the 2 hystrix threads running in &lt;tt&gt;HystrixProcessorCommand.run()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;HystrixProcessorCommand.()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be verified running the attached modified &lt;tt&gt;HystrixTimeoutWithFallbackTest&lt;/tt&gt; test inside &lt;tt&gt;components/camel-hystrix&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
